'''Timothée Hal Chalamet''' ({{IPAc-en|lang|ˈ|t|ɪ|m|ə|θ|i|_|ˈ|ʃ|æ|l|ə|m|eɪ}} {{respell|TIM|ə|thee|_|SHAL|ə|may}};{{efn|Chalamet when speaking English uses the pronunciation of "Timothy"<ref>{{Cite AV media |date=November 27, 2017 |title=Don't Talk {{!}} Armie Hammer and Timothée Chalamet from Call Me by Your Name |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=losJbtoNNfI&t=26s |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200911034224/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=losJbtoNNfI&t=26s |archive-date=September 11, 2020 |access-date=January 13, 2018 |publisher=Alamo Drafthouse |via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref><ref name="YouTube-Homeland">{{Cite web |date=October 1, 2014 |title=Timothée Chalamet on His Dream Roles and 'Homeland' |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uudre5SgXkI |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216141517/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uudre5SgXkI |archive-date=February 16, 2019 |access-date=February 17, 2019 |website=[[Teen Vogue]]}}</ref> as he finds approximating the French pronunciation {{IPA-fr|timɔte ʃalamɛ|}} "really pretentious" and "too much of an obligation".<ref>{{cite web|last=Barrett|first=Devin|date=February 6, 2018|url=https://vman.com/article/timothee-chalamet-frank-ocean/|title=Timothée Chalamet by Frank Ocean|work=V Man|access-date=February 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190217163401/https://vman.com/article/timothee-chalamet-frank-ocean/|archive-date=February 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>}} born December 27, 1995) is an American and French<!-- PLEASE SEE THE NEW TALK PAGE CONSENSUS. --> actor. He has received [[List of awards and nominations received by Timothée Chalamet|various accolades]], including nominations for an [[Academy Award]], three [[Golden Globe Awards]], and three [[BAFTA Film Awards]].

Chalamet began his career as a teenager in television, appearing in the drama series ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'' in 2012. In 2014, he made his film debut in the comedy-drama ''[[Men, Women & Children (film)|Men, Women & Children]]'' and appeared in [[Christopher Nolan]]'s science fiction film ''[[Interstellar (film)|Interstellar]]''. Chalamet came to international attention with the lead role of a lovestruck teenager in [[Luca Guadagnino]]'s coming-of-age film ''[[Call Me by Your Name (film)|Call Me by Your Name]]'' (2017), earning him a nomination for the [[Academy Award for Best Actor]]. Alongside supporting roles in [[Greta Gerwig]]'s films ''[[Lady Bird (film)|Lady Bird]]'' (2017) and ''[[Little Women (2019 film)|Little Women]]'' (2019), he took on starring roles as drug addict [[Nic Sheff]] in the biopic ''[[Beautiful Boy (2018 film)|Beautiful Boy]]'' (2018) and a young cannibal in Guadagnino's romantic horror film ''[[Bones and All]]'' (2022), which he also produced. Chalamet also began leading big-budget films, portraying [[Paul Atreides]] in [[Denis Villeneuve]]'s science fiction film ''[[Dune (2021 film)|Dune]]'' (2021) and [[Willy Wonka]] in [[Paul King (director)|Paul King]]'s musical fantasy film ''[[Wonka (film)|Wonka]]'' (2023).

On stage, Chalamet starred in [[John Patrick Shanley]]'s autobiographical play ''Prodigal Son'' in 2016, for which he won a [[Lucille Lortel Award]] and gained a nomination for a [[Drama League Award]]. Off-screen, he has been labeled as a [[sex symbol]] and a [[fashion icon]].

==Early life and education==
Chalamet was born on December 27, 1995, in New York City, and grew up in the federally subsidized artists' building [[Manhattan Plaza]] in [[Hell's Kitchen, Manhattan|Hell's Kitchen]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Timothée Chalamet |url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/person/timoth%C3%A9e-chalamet |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919100744/https://www.goldenglobes.com/person/timothee-chalamet |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=December 13, 2017 |publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]}}</ref><ref name="GQ" /> He has an elder sister, [[Pauline Chalamet]], who is an actress.<ref name="GQ" /> His mother, Nicole Flender, is a third-generation New Yorker, of half [[History of the Jews in Russia|Russian Jewish]] and half [[History of the Jews in Austria|Austrian Jewish]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kellaway |first=Kate |date=October 15, 2017 |title=Call Me By Your Name's Oscar-tipped double act on their summer of love |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/oct/15/armie-hammer-timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-interview |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919101438/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/oct/15/armie-hammer-timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-interview |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 13, 2018 |website=[[The Guardian]] |location=London}}</ref> She is a [[real estate agent]] at [[NRT (company)|The Corcoran Group]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gould Keil |first=Jennifer |date=March 7, 2018 |title=This fancy Upper West Side townhouse housed a sitcom star |url=https://nypost.com/2018/03/07/this-fancy-upper-west-side-townhouse-housed-a-sitcom-star/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324064321/https://nypost.com/2018/03/07/this-fancy-upper-west-side-townhouse-housed-a-sitcom-star/ |archive-date=March 24, 2020 |access-date=March 24, 2020 |publisher=New York Post}}</ref> and a former [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] dancer; Flender earned her bachelor's degree in French from [[Yale University]], and has been a language and dance teacher.<ref>{{Cite web |date=Fall 2014 |title=Yale Department of French |url=https://french.yale.edu/sites/default/files/files/newsletters/FrenchNews14F.pdf |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525070624/https://french.yale.edu/sites/default/files/files/newsletters/FrenchNews14F.pdf |archive-date=May 25, 2019 |access-date=May 15, 2020 |publisher=Yale University}}</ref><ref name="Liberation">{{Cite web |last=Piette |first=Jérémy |date=February 26, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet, appelez-le par&nbsp;son&nbsp;nom |trans-title=Timothée Chalamet, call him by his name |url=https://next.liberation.fr/cinema/2018/02/26/timothee-chalamet-appelez-le-par-son-nom_1632447 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919101929/https://next.liberation.fr/cinema/2018/02/26/timothee-chalamet-appelez-le-par-son-nom_1632447 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=March 2, 2018 |website=[[Libération]] |language=fr}}</ref> His French father, Marc Chalamet, is an editor for the [[UNICEF|United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF)]] and former New York correspondent for ''[[Le Parisien]]''.<ref name="GQ">{{Cite magazine |last=Riley |first=Daniel |date=February 14, 2018 |title=The Arrival of Timothée Chalamet |url=https://www.gq.com/story/timothee-chalamet-has-arrived |url-status=live |magazine=[[GQ]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919101700/https://www.gq.com/story/timothee-chalamet-has-arrived |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Belpeche |first=Stéphanie |date=February 28, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet, le nouveau chouchou de Hollywood |url=https://www.lejdd.fr/Culture/Cinema/timothee-chalamet-le-nouveau-chouchou-de-hollywood-3585155 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611234110/https://www.lejdd.fr/Culture/Cinema/timothee-chalamet-le-nouveau-chouchou-de-hollywood-3585155 |archive-date=June 11, 2020 |access-date=May 8, 2020 |publisher=Le Journal de Dimanche |language=fr}}</ref> Marc is from [[Nîmes]] and is of Protestant background.<ref name="Liberation" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=David |first=Keren |date=November 20, 2019 |title=Hollywood star Timothée Chalamet to take to the stage in London for acclaimed play |url=https://www.thejc.com/news/the-diary/hollywood-s-timothe-e-chalamet-to-star-in-london-stage-production-of-pulitzer-play-1.493379 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210722133156/https://www.thejc.com/news/the-diary/hollywood-s-timothe-e-chalamet-to-star-in-london-stage-production-of-pulitzer-play-1.493379 |archive-date=July 22, 2021 |access-date=July 22, 2021 |website=thejc.com |publisher=The Jewish Chronicle}}</ref> Timothée's paternal grandmother, who had moved to France, was originally Canadian.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Demars |first=Céline |date=March 3, 2018 |title=Les racines auvergnates de Timothée Chalamet, nouveau chouchou d'Hollywood à 22 ans |url=https://www.lamontagne.fr/chambon-sur-lignon/loisirs/people/2018/03/03/les-racines-auvergnates-de-timothee-chalamet-nouveau-chouchou-d-hollywood-a-22-ans_12759475.html#refresh |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919102512/https://www.lamontagne.fr/chambon-sur-lignon/loisirs/people/2018/03/03/les-racines-auvergnates-de-timothee-chalamet-nouveau-chouchou-d-hollywood-a-22-ans_12759475.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=June 15, 2018 |website=[[La Montagne (newspaper)|La Montagne]] |language=fr}}</ref> On his mother's side, he is a nephew of husband-and-wife filmmakers and producers [[Rodman Flender]] and [[Amy Lippman]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Hautman |first=Nicholas |date=January 1, 2020 |title=Timothee Chalamet's Rise From Theater Kid to Critical Darling |url=https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/pictures/timothee-chalamets-rise-from-theater-kid-to-critical-darling/ |url-status=live |magazine=Us Weekly |publisher=A360 Media LLC |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111183433/https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/pictures/timothee-chalamets-rise-from-theater-kid-to-critical-darling/ |archive-date=January 11, 2022 |access-date=January 11, 2022}}</ref>

Chalamet is bilingual in English and French,{{efn|On ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'', Chalamet said he estimates his fluency in French to be approximately 97%.<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 6, 2019 |title=You're Probably Pronouncing Timothée Chalamet's Name Wrong |url=https://screenrant.com/timothee-chalamet-name-pronunciation/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215201721/https://screenrant.com/timothee-chalamet-name-pronunciation/ |archive-date=February 15, 2020 |access-date=February 15, 2020 |publisher=ScreenRant.com}}</ref>}}<ref>{{Cite web |last=Boudsocq |first=Stéphane |date=February 28, 2018 |title="La Ch'tite famille" et "Call Me By Your Name" dans les sorties de la semaine |url=https://www.rtl.fr/culture/cine-series/la-ch-tite-famille-et-call-me-by-your-name-dans-les-sorties-de-la-semaine-7792443086 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919122823/https://www.rtl.fr/culture/cine-series/la-ch-tite-famille-et-call-me-by-your-name-dans-les-sorties-de-la-semaine-7792443086 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=June 15, 2018 |website=[[RTL (French radio)|RTL]] |language=fr}}</ref> and holds dual United States and French citizenship due to his French father.<ref>Various sources:
* {{Cite web |last=Drell |first=Cady |date=July 13, 2018 |title=This Week in Timothée Hal Chalamet, July 13 Edition |url=https://www.marieclaire.com/celebrity/a22131876/timothee-chalamet-july-13/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327090332/https://www.marieclaire.com/celebrity/a22131876/timothee-chalamet-july-13/ |archive-date=March 27, 2019 |access-date=March 23, 2019 |website=[[Marie Claire]] |language=en-US |quote=...from France, where incidentally, Timothée Chalamet's father was born. (That’s why Timmy has dual citizenship and speaks fluent French...}}
* {{Cite web|url=https://www.lexpress.fr/culture/cinema/oscars-hollywood-s-arrache-timothee-chalamet-un-franco-americain-de-22-ans_1988833.html|title=Oscars: Hollywood s'arrache Timothée Chalamet, un Franco-Américain de 22 ans|date=March 4, 2018|website=[[L'Express]]|language=fr|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322025353/https://www.lexpress.fr/culture/cinema/oscars-hollywood-s-arrache-timothee-chalamet-un-franco-americain-de-22-ans_1988833.html|archive-date=March 22, 2019|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|url=https://www.lesinrocks.com/2018/02/06/cinema/timothee-chalamet-confessions-dun-wonder-boy-111042846/|title=Rencontre avec Timothée Chalamet, "the next big thing" du cinéma hollywoodien|website=Les Inrocks|language=fr-FR|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613150042/https://www.lesinrocks.com/2018/02/06/cinema/timothee-chalamet-confessions-dun-wonder-boy-111042846/|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|url=https://www.service-public.fr/particuliers/vosdroits/F3068|title=Dans quels cas un enfant est-il Français ?|website=www.service-public.fr|language=Fr|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323002715/https://www.service-public.fr/particuliers/vosdroits/F3068|archive-date=March 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Growing up, Chalamet spent summers in [[Le Chambon-sur-Lignon]],<ref name="Verge">{{Cite web |last=Herman |first=James Patrick |date=February 6, 2015 |title=Timothée Chalamet – Takes off in Interstellar |url=https://www.verge.is/timothee-chalamet-interstellar |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206034251/https://www.verge.is/timothee-chalamet-interstellar |archive-date=February 6, 2015 |website=Verge Magazine}}</ref> a small French village two hours away from [[Lyon]], at the home of his paternal grandparents. He stated that his time in France led to cross-cultural identity issues.<ref name="Marotta">{{Cite web |last=Marotta |first=Jenna |date=November 17, 2017 |title='Call Me by Your Name': Timothée Chalamet is Learning How to Be a Man, Onscreen and Off |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/11/timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-1201898370/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919103035/https://www.indiewire.com/2017/11/timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-1201898370/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=January 23, 2018 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Lussier |first=Marc-André |date=December 15, 2017 |title=Timothée Chalamet, nouvelle étoile du cinéma mondial |url=https://plus.lapresse.ca/screens/352b92c7-fae8-4017-b421-b3f6e7c19327__7C___0.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919103303/https://plus.lapresse.ca/screens/352b92c7-fae8-4017-b421-b3f6e7c19327__7C___0.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=January 23, 2018 |website=[[La Presse (Canadian newspaper)|La Presse]] |language=fr}}</ref>
Chalamet attended PS 87 William T. Sherman School for elementary school, and later the selective Delta program at MS 54 Booker T. Washington Middle School, which he described as miserable due to the lack of a creative outlet within the school's academically rigorous environment.<ref name="Horowitz">{{Cite podcast |url=https://www.stitcher.com/podcast/panoply/happy-sad-confused/e/52486078 |title=Happy Sad Confused |website=[[Stitcher Radio|Stitcher]] |publisher=[[MTV]] |host=Josh Horowitz |date=December 8, 2017 |access-date=April 25, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426144632/https://www.stitcher.com/podcast/panoply/happy-sad-confused/e/52486078 |archive-date=April 26, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Heath Ledger]]'s performance as the [[Joker (The Dark Knight)|Joker]] in ''[[The Dark Knight]]'' (2008) inspired him to pursue a career in acting.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Earl |first=William |date=January 7, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet Reveals How Heath Ledger's 'Dark Knight' Performance Inspired Him To Act |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/01/timothee-chalamet-heath-ledger-the-dark-knight-1201914412/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113215553/https://www.indiewire.com/2018/01/timothee-chalamet-heath-ledger-the-dark-knight-1201914412/ |archive-date=January 13, 2022 |access-date=January 13, 2022 |website=IndieWire}}</ref> He applied to [[Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School|Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School of Music & Art and Performing Arts]]. His acceptance into the school was a turning point in his appreciation for acting.<ref>{{Cite web |date=September 19, 2013 |title=PeopleHop: Timothée Chalamet |url=https://bwog.com/2013/09/19/peoplehop-timothee-chalamet/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919103910/http://bwog.com/2013/09/19/peoplehop-timothee-chalamet/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 27, 2017 |website=[[Bwog]]}}</ref> His sophomore-year drama teacher at LaGuardia<ref>{{Cite podcast |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/awards-chatter-podcast-timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-1082776 |title='Awards Chatter' Podcast — Timothee Chalamet ('Call Me by Your Name') |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |host=Scott Feinberg |date=February 19, 2018 |time=34:04–34:17 |access-date=June 17, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919104013/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/awards-chatter-podcast-timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-1082776 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> was so impressed by his audition that he insisted on Chalamet's acceptance into the school, even though he had been rejected in the interview (due to his middle school record),<ref name="Broadway">{{Cite web |title=Prodigal Son Playwright John Patrick Shanley & Star Timothee Chalamet on the Pain, Poetry & Pride of Revisiting 15 |url=https://www.broadway.com/buzz/184066/prodigal-son-playwright-john-patrick-shanley-star-timothee-chalamet-on-the-pain-poetry-pride-of-revisiting-15/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215201723/https://www.broadway.com/buzz/184066/prodigal-son-playwright-john-patrick-shanley-star-timothee-chalamet-on-the-pain-poetry-pride-of-revisiting-15/ |archive-date=February 15, 2020 |access-date=February 15, 2020 |publisher=[[John Gore Organization]]}}</ref> saying: "I gave him the highest score I've ever given a kid auditioning."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Duboff |first=Josh |date=January 19, 2018 |title=Meet Timothée Chalamet and Ansel Elgort's High-School Drama Teacher, Mr. Shifman |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/01/timothee-chalamet-ansel-elgort-laguardia-high-school-drama-teacher-harry-shifman |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919104340/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/01/timothee-chalamet-ansel-elgort-laguardia-high-school-drama-teacher-harry-shifman |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=June 16, 2018 |website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]}}</ref> During high school, Chalamet dated [[Madonna]]'s daughter [[Lourdes Leon|Lola Leon]], a fellow student, for a year.<ref name="GQ" /> He starred in school musicals as Emcee in ''[[Cabaret (musical)|Cabaret]]'' and Oscar Lindquist in ''[[Sweet Charity]]'', graduating in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Freedman |first=Adrianna Chaviva |date=February 5, 2018 |title=Timothee Chalamet Is The Youngest In 80 Years To Be Nominated For Best Actor |url=https://forward.com/schmooze/393676/timothee-chalamet-is-the-youngest-in-80-years-to-be-nominated-for-best-acto/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919104548/https://forward.com/schmooze/393676/timothee-chalamet-is-the-youngest-in-80-years-to-be-nominated-for-best-acto/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 27, 2018 |website=[[The Forward]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Bell |first=Crystal |date=February 27, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet Is Still Learning How To Be A Leading Man |url=https://www.mtv.com/news/3066484/timothee-chalamet-interview-call-me-by-your-name/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919104722/http://www.mtv.com/news/3066484/timothee-chalamet-interview-call-me-by-your-name/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 25, 2018 |website=[[MTV News]]}}</ref> He is also a [[YoungArts]] alumnus.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2013 YoungArts Winners |url=https://youngarts.org/storage/app/media/Past%20Winners/2013%20-%20YoungArts%20Winners.pdf |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919104844/https://youngarts.org/storage/app/media/Past%20Winners/2013%20-%20YoungArts%20Winners.pdf |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=December 9, 2017 |website=[[YoungArts]]}}</ref>

After high school, Chalamet, then 17, attended [[Columbia University]] for one year, majoring in [[cultural anthropology]], and was a resident of [[Hartley Hall]].<ref name="Verge" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=West |first=James |date=March 31, 2018 |title=Back in the day with Timothée Chalamet |url=https://hero-magazine.com/article/116930/back-in-the-day-with-timothee-chalamet/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919104917/http://hero-magazine.com/article/116930/back-in-the-day-with-timothee-chalamet/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=March 31, 2018 |website=[[Hero (magazine)|HERO Magazine]] |publication-date=April 30, 2015 |quote=I'm at Columbia University in New York, majoring in cultural anthropology. |issue=13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Druckman |first=Bella |date=August 5, 2021 |title=Top 10 Haunts and Hangouts of the Beat Generation |url=https://untappedcities.com/2021/08/05/haunts-and-hangouts-beat-generation/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211110180759/https://untappedcities.com/2021/08/05/haunts-and-hangouts-beat-generation/ |archive-date=November 10, 2021 |access-date=November 10, 2021 |website=Untapped New York |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Walker |first=Miyoki |date=October 23, 2018 |title=Where Did Timothée Chalamet Live? |url=https://bwog.com/2018/10/where-did-timothee-chalamet-live/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211110181025/https://bwog.com/2018/10/where-did-timothee-chalamet-live/ |archive-date=November 10, 2021 |access-date=November 10, 2021 |website=Bwog.com}}</ref> He later transferred to [[New York University]]'s [[Gallatin School of Individualized Study]] to pursue his acting career more freely,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kaufman |first=Amy |date=November 17, 2017 |title=Timothée Chalamet is Hollywood's next big thing with 'Call Me by Your Name' and 'Lady Bird' |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-ca-mn-timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-20171116-story.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919105008/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-ca-mn-timothee-chalamet-call-me-by-your-name-20171116-story.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 28, 2018 |website=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref> having found it difficult to assimilate to Columbia directly after filming ''[[Interstellar (film)|Interstellar]]''.<ref name="InterviewMagMatt">{{Cite web |last=McConaughey |first=Matthew |date=June 2, 2017 |title=Timothée Chalamet |url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/timothee-chalamet |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616014542/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/timothee-chalamet |archive-date=June 16, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]] |quote=Anyway, I did a year at Columbia, and I just kind of floundered. Maybe it wasn’t the right place for me. [...] Columbia takes a wholehearted academic commitment that I think I have in me, but it was just not where my mind was at the time. [...] It was just hard.}}</ref> Upon leaving Columbia, Chalamet moved to [[Concourse, Bronx]].<ref name="GQ" /><ref name="TimeOut">{{Cite web |last=Rothkopf |first=Joshua |date=October 5, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet: 'I don't know how the f**k any of this happened' |url=https://www.timeout.com/london/film/timothee-chalamet-i-dont-know-how-the-fuck-any-of-this-happened |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115225943/https://www.timeout.com/london/film/timothee-chalamet-i-dont-know-how-the-fuck-any-of-this-happened |archive-date=January 15, 2020 |access-date=January 15, 2020 |website=TimeOut London |publisher=TimeOut Group Plc}}</ref>

==Career==
===2008–2016: Early roles===
[[File:Men Women and Children 16 (15250911126).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Chalamet at the [[2014 Toronto International Film Festival]]]]
As a child, Chalamet appeared in several commercials and acted in two horror short films called ''Sweet Tooth'' and ''Clown'', before making his television debut on an episode of the long-running [[police procedural]] series ''[[Law & Order]]'' (2009), playing a murder victim.<ref name="Verge" /> He followed this with a minor role in the television film ''[[Loving Leah]]'' (2009). In 2011, he made his stage debut in the [[Off-Broadway]] play ''The Talls'', a [[Coming-of-age story|coming-of-age]] comedy set in the 1970s, in which he played a sexually curious 12-year-old. The chief theatre critic of ''[[New York Daily News]]'' wrote: "Chalamet hilariously captures a tween's awakening curiosities about sex."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Isherwood |first=Charles |date=August 16, 2011 |title=A 17-Year-Old Beanstalk From a Wholesome '70s Family Is Eager to Go Far Out |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/08/17/theater/reviews/the-talls-by-anna-kerrigan-review.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919105109/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/08/17/theater/reviews/the-talls-by-anna-kerrigan-review.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref name="NYDN-TheTalls">{{Cite web |last=Dziemianowicz |first=Joe |date=August 16, 2011 |title='The Talls' review: Family drama is familiar story, but excellent acting gives play extra boost |url=https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/talls-review-family-drama-familiar-story-excellent-acting-play-extra-boost-article-1.950067 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919105809/https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/talls-review-family-drama-familiar-story-excellent-acting-play-extra-boost-article-1.950067 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[New York Daily News]]}}</ref> In 2012, he had recurring roles in the drama series ''[[Royal Pains]]'' and the thriller series ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'', in which he played [[Finn Walden]], the rebellious son of the Vice President. Along with the rest of the cast, Chalamet was nominated for a [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|SAG Award for Best Ensemble]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Blake |first=Meredith |date=December 12, 2012 |title=SAG award nominations: Cable dramas and network sitcoms dominate |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2012/dec/12/entertainment/la-et-st-sag-award-nominations-tv-20121212 |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919123054/http://articles.latimes.com/2012/dec/12/entertainment/la-et-st-sag-award-nominations-tv-20121212 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref>

In 2014, Chalamet made his feature film debut in a minor role in [[Jason Reitman]]'s ''[[Men, Women & Children (film)|Men, Women & Children]]''.<ref name="Metacritic-MenWomenChildren">{{Cite web |title=Men, Women & Children Reviews |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/men-women-children |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919112229/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/men-women-children |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=September 19, 2018 |website=[[Metacritic]]}}</ref> In the same year, he played the role of Tom Cooper, the son of [[Matthew McConaughey]]'s character, in [[Christopher Nolan]]'s ''[[Interstellar (film)|Interstellar]]''.<ref name="TheWrap-Interstellar">{{Cite web |last=Sneider |first=Jeff |date=July 15, 2013 |title=Christopher Nolan Casting Young 'Homeland' Actor in 'Interstellar' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.thewrap.com/christopher-nolan-casting-young-homeland-actor-interstellar-exclusive-103286/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919110057/https://www.thewrap.com/christopher-nolan-casting-young-homeland-actor-interstellar-exclusive-103286/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[TheWrap]]}}</ref> The film received positive reviews, with critics praising the cast's performances, and grossed over $700 million worldwide.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Greene |first=Andy |date=April 8, 2015 |title=Readers' Poll: The 20 Best Movies of the 2010s So Far |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-lists/readers-poll-the-20-best-movies-of-the-2010s-so-far-175557/interstellar-2014-28802/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919110144/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-lists/readers-poll-the-20-best-movies-of-the-2010s-so-far-175557/interstellar-2014-28802/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=July 21, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Anand |first=Gautam |date=November 6, 2014 |title=Review: 'Interstellar' is Awe-Inspiring |url=http://www.thecinemaholic.com/movie-review-interstellar/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222195006/http://www.thecinemaholic.com/movie-review-interstellar/ |archive-date=February 22, 2017 |access-date=July 21, 2017 |website=The Cinemaholic}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Travers |first=Peter |author-link=Peter Travers |date=December 4, 2014 |title=10 Best Movies of 2014 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-lists/10-best-movies-of-2014-141411/interstellar-166956/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919110755/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-lists/10-best-movies-of-2014-141411/interstellar-166956/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=July 21, 2017}}</ref> Also in 2014, Chalamet had a supporting role in ''[[Worst Friends (2014 film)|Worst Friends]]'', a comedy which had a limited theatrical release and received positive reviews.<ref name="RottenTomatoes-WorstFriends">{{Cite web |title=Worst Friends (2014) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/worst_friends/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919113126/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/worst_friends/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 12, 2017 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=November 4, 2014 }}</ref> In the next year, Chalamet co-starred in [[Andrew Droz Palermo]]'s fantasy thriller ''[[One & Two]]'', which premiered at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]], where it received mixed reviews, before its limited theatrical release.<ref name="Variety-OneTwo">{{Cite web |last=Debruge |first=Peter |date=February 12, 2015 |title=Berlin Film Review: 'One & Two' |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/berlin-film-review-one-two-1201432196/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919135100/https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/berlin-film-review-one-two-1201432196/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=September 19, 2018 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Gold |first=Daniel M. |date=August 13, 2015 |title=Review: 'One & Two' Exposes Dangers of Trying to Control Teenagers |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/14/movies/review-one-two-exposes-dangers-of-trying-to-control-teenagers.html? |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919135434/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/14/movies/review-one-two-exposes-dangers-of-trying-to-control-teenagers.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=September 19, 2018 |website=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=One & Two (2015) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/one_and_two_2015/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919113255/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/one_and_two_2015/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=December 24, 2015 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=August 14, 2015 }}</ref> His next role was playing the teenage version of [[James Franco]]'s character, [[Stephen Elliott (author)|Stephen Elliott]], in [[Pamela Romanowsky]]'s ''[[The Adderall Diaries (film)|The Adderall Diaries]]''.<ref name="RottenTomatoes-AdderallDiaries">{{Cite web |title=The Adderall Diaries (2016) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_adderall_diaries/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919113437/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_adderall_diaries/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 19, 2016 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=April 15, 2016 }}</ref> In his final role of 2015, Chalamet played Charlie Cooper, the sullen grandson of [[Diane Keaton]] and [[John Goodman]]'s characters in the Christmas comedy ''[[Love the Coopers]]'', which received negative reviews.<ref name="RottenTomatoes-LoveCoopers">{{Cite web |title=Love the Coopers (2015) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/love_the_coopers/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919113620/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/love_the_coopers/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 24, 2016 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=November 13, 2015 }}</ref>

In 2016, Chalamet starred as Jim Quinn in the autobiographical play ''Prodigal Son'' at [[Manhattan Theatre Club]]. Handpicked by its playwright and director [[John Patrick Shanley]] and producer [[Scott Rudin]], Chalamet portrayed a younger Shanley, a misfit [[Bronx]] kid in a prestigious [[New Hampshire]] prep school set in 1963.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Timothee Chalamet |url=https://alumniandfriends.org/timothee-chalamet-lag-13-in-prodigal-son/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919114349/https://alumniandfriends.org/timothee-chalamet-lag-13-in-prodigal-son/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=September 2, 2017 |website=[[Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School|Alumni and Friends of LaGuardia High School]]}}</ref> His performance was praised and won him the [[Lucille Lortel Award|Lucille Lortel Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Play]], in addition to a nomination for the [[Drama League Award|Drama League Award for Distinguished Performance]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rooney |first=David |date=May 1, 2016 |title=Lucille Lortel Awards: The Complete Winners List |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/lucille-lortel-awards-full-winners-887915 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919114519/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/lucille-lortel-awards-full-winners-887915 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Cox |first=Gordon |date=April 20, 2016 |title=Drama League Awards Nominations: Jessica Lange, Lupita Nyong'o, Jesse Tyler Ferguson and Lots More (FULL LIST) |url=https://variety.com/2016/legit/news/drama-league-awards-nominations-2016-full-list-1201757445/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919114615/https://variety.com/2016/legit/news/drama-league-awards-nominations-2016-full-list-1201757445/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 23, 2017 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Brantley |first=Ben |date=February 9, 2016 |title=Review: 'Prodigal Son,' John Patrick Shanley's Exploration of the Student He Once Was |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/10/theater/review-prodigal-son-john-patrick-shanleys-exploration-of-the-student-he-once-was.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919114747/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/10/theater/review-prodigal-son-john-patrick-shanleys-exploration-of-the-student-he-once-was.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref name="HollywoodReporter-ProdigalSon">{{Cite web |last=Rooney |first=David |date=February 9, 2016 |title='Prodigal Son': Theater Review |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/john-patrick-shanleys-prodigal-son-862791 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919114803/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/john-patrick-shanleys-prodigal-son-862791 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 9, 2017 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> Chalamet also co-starred opposite [[Lily Rabe]] in [[Julia Hart]]'s ''[[Miss Stevens]]'' as the troubled student Billy Mitman. Stephen Farber of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' described Chalamet's act as "compelling" and "startling", with his character's speech from ''[[Death of a Salesman]]'' as among the best he has ever seen.<ref name="HollywoodReporter-MissStevens">{{Cite web |last=Farber |first=Stephen |date=March 14, 2016 |title='Miss Stevens': SXSW Review |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/miss-stevens-sxsw-review-875024 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919114903/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/miss-stevens-sxsw-review-875024 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 16, 2017 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> [[Stephen Holden]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'' compared him to [[James Dean]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Holden |first=Stephen |date=September 15, 2016 |title=Review: In 'Miss Stevens,' a Chaperone Greets Temptation |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/16/movies/miss-stevens-review.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919114916/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/16/movies/miss-stevens-review.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 16, 2017 |website=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref>

===2017–2020: Breakthrough and rise to prominence===
[[File:Timothée Chalamet in 2018 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Chalamet at the [[2018 Toronto International Film Festival]]]]
After being attached to the project for three years, Chalamet starred in [[Luca Guadagnino]]'s ''[[Call Me by Your Name (film)|Call Me by Your Name]]'', based on the novel [[Call Me by Your Name (novel)|of the same name]] by [[André Aciman]].<ref name="FilmStage-CMBYN">{{Cite web |last=Raup |first=Jordan |date=May 23, 2016 |title=Michael Stuhlbarg, Armie Hammer & More Leading Luca Guadagnino's 'Call Me By Your Name' |url=https://thefilmstage.com/news/michael-stuhlbarg-armie-hammer-more-leading-luca-guadagninos-call-me-by-your-name/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919115040/https://thefilmstage.com/news/michael-stuhlbarg-armie-hammer-more-leading-luca-guadagninos-call-me-by-your-name/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=June 5, 2016 |website=The Film Stage}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Vivarelli |first=Nick |date=February 13, 2017 |title=Berlinale: Luca Guadagnino on Why 'Call Me by Your Name' Strikes Such Deep Chords |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/global/berlinale-luca-guadagnino-call-me-by-your-name-1201986720/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919115104/https://variety.com/2017/film/global/berlinale-luca-guadagnino-call-me-by-your-name-1201986720/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=August 17, 2017 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> The story revolves around Elio Perlman, a young man living in Italy during the 1980s, who falls in love with Oliver ([[Armie Hammer]]), a university student who has come to stay with his family. In preparation, Chalamet learned to speak Italian, as well as to play the piano and guitar.<ref name=InterviewMagMatt/> ''Call Me by Your Name'' premiered at the [[2017 Sundance Film Festival]] to critical acclaim;<ref>{{Cite web |last=Erbland |first=Kate |date=February 13, 2017 |title=Call Me By Your Name: Luca Guadagnino, Armie Hammer Press Conference |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/02/call-me-by-your-name-luca-guadagnino-armie-hammer-press-conference-1201781749/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502173144/https://www.indiewire.com/2017/02/call-me-by-your-name-luca-guadagnino-armie-hammer-press-conference-1201781749/ |archive-date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref> critics particularly highlighted Chalamet's performance.<ref>{{Cite web |date=November 8, 2017 |title=Next Gen Talent 2017: Hollywood's Rising Stars 35 and Under |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/next-gen-talent-2017-hollywoods-rising-stars-35-under-1055922 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210419170919/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/next-gen-talent-2017-hollywoods-rising-stars-35-under-1055922 |archive-date=April 19, 2021 |access-date=May 3, 2021 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Hurly |first=Adam |date=November 24, 2017 |title=Get the Cut: Armie Hammer and Timothée Chalamet's Call Me by Your Name '80s Hair |url=https://www.gq.com/story/get-the-cut-call-me-by-your-name-timothee-chalamet-armie-hammer-hair |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171130145241/https://www.gq.com/story/get-the-cut-call-me-by-your-name-timothee-chalamet-armie-hammer-hair |archive-date=November 30, 2017 |access-date=September 11, 2020 |website=[[GQ]]}}</ref> Olly Richards of ''[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]]'' wrote: "In a film in which every performance is terrific, Chalamet makes the rest look like they're acting. He alone would make the film worth watching".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Richards |first=Olly |date=October 23, 2017 |title='Call Me By Your Name' Review |url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/call-name/review/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919115830/https://www.empireonline.com/movies/call-name/review/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=October 23, 2017 |website=[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]]}}</ref> Jon Frosch of ''The Hollywood Reporter'' stated that no performance during the year "felt as emotionally, physically and intellectually alive" and included Chalamet in the magazine's list of the best performances of the year.<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 13, 2017 |title=Hollywood Reporter Film Critics Pick the 13 Best Performances of the Year |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hollywood-reporter-film-critics-pick-13-best-performances-year-1066626/item/mary-j-blige-thr-critics-best-performances-2017-1066595 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919115846/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hollywood-reporter-film-critics-pick-13-best-performances-year-1066626/item/mary-j-blige-thr-critics-best-performances-2017-1066595 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=June 14, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' and ''The New York Times'' also featured him in such lists.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Zacharek |first=Stephanie |author-link=Stephanie Zacharek |date=December 7, 2017 |title=The Top 10 Movie Performances of 2017 |url=https://time.com/5047536/top-10-movie-performances-2017/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211014120655/https://time.com/5047536/top-10-movie-performances-2017/ |archive-date=October 14, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |url-access=limited}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Scott |first1=A. O. |author-link=A. O. Scott |last2=Morris |first2=Wesley |author-link2=Wesley Morris |date=December 7, 2017 |title=The 10 Best Actors of the Year |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/07/magazine/the-10-best-actors-of-the-year.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919120046/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/07/magazine/the-10-best-actors-of-the-year.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=December 8, 2017 |website=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> He won the [[Gotham Independent Film Award for Breakthrough Actor]] and the [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Male Lead]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gettell |first=Oliver |date=November 27, 2017 |title=''Call Me By Your Name'' takes top prize at 2017 Gotham Awards |url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/11/27/gotham-awards-2017-winners-list/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220224946/https://ew.com/movies/2017/11/27/gotham-awards-2017-winners-list/ |archive-date=February 20, 2018 |access-date=November 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |title=Independent Spirit Awards winners 2018: See the full list |url=https://ew.com/awards/2018/03/03/independent-spirit-awards-2018-winners-list/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804232534/http://ew.com/awards/2018/03/03/independent-spirit-awards-2018-winners-list/ |archive-date=August 4, 2018 |access-date=April 6, 2021}}</ref> and received nominations for the [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Actor|Critics' Choice Movie Award]], [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor – Motion Picture Drama|Golden Globe Award]], [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Leading Role|SAG Award]], [[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role|BAFTA Award]], and [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Academy Award]], all for Best Actor.<ref name="Oscars2017">{{Cite web |last=Haylock |first=Zoe |date=February 23, 2018 |title=Timothee Chalamet – Oscars: 11 of 2018's Historic Nominees |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/oscars-2018-record-breaking-nominees-1081765/item/timothee-chalamet-2018-oscars-milestones-1081737 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919120349/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/oscars-2018-record-breaking-nominees-1081765/item/timothee-chalamet-2018-oscars-milestones-1081737 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=March 4, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref><ref name="GG2017">{{Cite news |last1=Merry |first1=Stephanie |last2=Yahr |first2=Emily |date=December 11, 2017 |title=Golden Globes nominations 2018: Complete list of nominations |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/12/11/golden-globes-nominations-2018-complete-coverage/ |url-status=live |access-date=December 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220224422/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/12/11/golden-globes-nominations-2018-complete-coverage/ |archive-date=February 20, 2018}}</ref><ref name="SAG2017">{{Cite web |last=Nordyke |first=Kimberly |date=January 21, 2018 |title=SAG Awards: Complete List of Winners |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/sag-award-winners-2018-full-list-1067861 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123145143/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/sag-award-winners-2018-full-list-1067861 |archive-date=January 23, 2018 |access-date=February 21, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref><ref name="BAFTA2017">{{Cite web |date=February 18, 2018 |title=BAFTA Awards: 2018 Complete Winners List |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/bafta-awards-2018-complete-winners-list-1202702940/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220220754/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/bafta-awards-2018-complete-winners-list-1202702940/ |archive-date=February 20, 2018 |access-date=February 20, 2018 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> He is the [[List of oldest and youngest Academy Award winners and nominees#Youngest nominees 2|third-youngest]] person to be nominated for an Academy Award for Best Actor as well as the youngest since [[Mickey Rooney|19-year-old Mickey Rooney]] in ''[[Babes in Arms (film)|Babes in Arms]]'' in [[12th Academy Awards|1939]].<ref name="Oscars2017" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sharf |first=Zack |date=March 3, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet Wins Indie Spirit Award for Best Actor, Becomes Third Youngest Winner in History |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/03/timothee-chalamet-wins-indie-spirit-award-best-actor-1201934496/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802220622/https://www.indiewire.com/2018/03/timothee-chalamet-wins-indie-spirit-award-best-actor-1201934496/ |archive-date=August 2, 2018 |access-date=March 12, 2021 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref>

In his second film of 2017, Chalamet played Daniel, a gawky teenager who gets swept up in the drug-dealing business over the course of a summer, in Elijah Bynum's directorial debut, ''[[Hot Summer Nights (film)|Hot Summer Nights]]''. It received a limited theatrical release in 2018 and generated mixed reviews from critics, though Chalamet received praise from K. Austin Collins of ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'', who called the "sensitivity" in his performance "something special".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Evans |first=Greg |date=April 12, 2018 |title='Hot Summer Nights' Trailer: Timothée Chalamet Gets Tangled Up In Weed |url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/timothee-chalamet-hot-summer-nights-trailer-tangled-up-in-weed-1202362873/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919120552/https://deadline.com/2018/04/timothee-chalamet-hot-summer-nights-trailer-tangled-up-in-weed-1202362873/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=April 12, 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Hot Summer Nights Reviews |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/hot-summer-nights |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919120735/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/hot-summer-nights |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=July 29, 2018 |website=[[Metacritic]]}}</ref><ref name="VF-HotSummerNights">{{Cite web |last=Collins |first=K. Austin |date=July 26, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet Makes the Overwrought Hot Summer Nights Worthwhile |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/07/hot-summer-nights-review |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919120813/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/07/hot-summer-nights-review |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=July 29, 2018 |website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]}}</ref> Later that year, he played Kyle Scheible, a rich hipster in a band and a love interest of [[Saoirse Ronan]]'s character in ''[[Lady Bird (film)|Lady Bird]]'', the solo directorial debut of [[Greta Gerwig]].<ref name="IndieWire-LadyBird">{{Cite web |last=Kohn |first=Eric |date=September 2, 2017 |title=Saoirse Ronan Scores Her Greatest Role In Greta Gerwig's Winning Directorial Debut 'Lady Bird' — Review |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/09/lady-bird-review-saoirse-ronan-greta-gerwig-telluride-2017-1201872501/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919120919/https://www.indiewire.com/2017/09/lady-bird-review-saoirse-ronan-greta-gerwig-telluride-2017-1201872501/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=September 2, 2017 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref> Critics praised the ensemble cast, with [[Ty Burr]] of ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' taking particular note of Chalamet's "hilarious" performance.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Burr |first=Ty |date=November 8, 2017 |title='Lady Bird' a wise, funny, empathetic tale from Greta Gerwig |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/movies/2017/11/08/lady-bird-wise-funny-empathetic-tale-from-greta-gerwig/SvM1mvwCM7hEiZR2oUaImM/story.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919120954/https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/movies/2017/11/08/lady-bird-wise-funny-empathetic-tale-from-greta-gerwig/SvM1mvwCM7hEiZR2oUaImM/story.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=November 8, 2017 |website=[[The Boston Globe]]}}</ref> In his final film of 2017, [[Scott Cooper (director)|Scott Cooper]]'s western ''[[Hostiles (film)|Hostiles]]'', Chalamet played a young soldier named Philippe DeJardin, alongside [[Christian Bale]].<ref name="Marotta" />

In 2018, Chalamet joined the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |date=June 25, 2018 |title=Movie Academy Invites Record 928 For Membership |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/movie-academy-invites-record-928-members-1202416895/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919121110/https://deadline.com/2018/06/movie-academy-invites-record-928-members-1202416895/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=June 25, 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> Later that year, Chalamet portrayed [[Nic Sheff]], a teenager addicted to [[methamphetamine]] who shares a strained relationship with his father, the journalist [[David Sheff]] (portrayed by [[Steve Carell]]), in the drama ''[[Beautiful Boy (2018 film)|Beautiful Boy]]''. Directed by [[Felix Van Groeningen]], the film is based on a pair of memoirs—the elder Sheff's [[Beautiful Boy: A Father's Journey Through His Son's Addiction|memoir of the same name]] and ''Tweak: Growing Up on Methamphetamines'' by Nic Sheff.<ref name="HollywoodReporter-BeautifulBoy">{{Cite web |last=Ford |first=Rebecca |date=February 6, 2017 |title=Sundance Breakout Timothee Chalamet Joining Steve Carell in 'Beautiful Boy' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sundance-breakout-timothee-chalamet-joining-steve-carell-beautiful-boy-971156 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919121125/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sundance-breakout-timothee-chalamet-joining-steve-carell-beautiful-boy-971156 |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=March 27, 2017 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> [[Owen Glieberman]] of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' drew comparisons with Chalamet's performance in ''Call Me by Your Name'', stating that "Nic, in his muffled millennial James Dean way, [as] skittery and self-involved" is a transformation from the "marvelous directness" he displayed in the role of Elio Perlman.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Glieberman |first=Owen |author-link=Owen Glieberman |date=September 7, 2018 |title=Toronto Film Review: 'Beautiful Boy' |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/reviews/beautiful-boy-review-timothee-chalamet-1202932186/ |url-status=live |access-date=September 16, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919121636/https://variety.com/2018/film/reviews/beautiful-boy-review-timothee-chalamet-1202932186/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018}}</ref> He received nominations for Best Supporting Actor at the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor – Motion Picture|Golden Globe]], [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Supporting Role|SAG]], and [[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role|BAFTA]] award ceremonies.<ref name="BB2019">{{Cite news |last=Gillespie |first=Katherine |date=January 23, 2019 |title=Where's Timothée Chalamet Oscar Nod for 'Beautiful Boy'? |url=https://www.papermag.com/timothee-chalamet-oscars-2626830469.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130173933/https://www.papermag.com/timothee-chalamet-oscars-2626830469.html |archive-date=November 30, 2020 |access-date=March 20, 2021 |website=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]}}</ref>

[[File:티모시 샬라메 (Timothee Chalamet) '더 킹 헨리 5세' 04.png|thumb|upright|Chalamet promoting ''[[The King (2019 film)|The King]]'' at the [[24th Busan International Film Festival|2019 Busan International Film Festival]]]]

The following year, Chalamet starred in [[Woody Allen]]'s romantic comedy ''[[A Rainy Day in New York]]''.<ref name="rainynewyork">{{Cite web |last=Vivarelli |first=Nick |date=May 5, 2019 |title=Woody Allen's 'A Rainy Day in New York' to be Released in Italy (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/woody-allen-a-rainy-day-in-new-york-released-italy-europe-1203205453/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190505123056/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/woody-allen-a-rainy-day-in-new-york-released-italy-europe-1203205453/ |archive-date=May 5, 2019 |access-date=May 5, 2019 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> The [[Me Too movement]] prompted a resurgence of the [[Woody Allen sexual abuse allegation|1992 sexual abuse allegation]] against Allen. Chalamet said he was unable to answer questions about working with Allen due to his contractual obligations; the ''[[Huffington Post]]'' obtained a copy of Chalamet's contract which disputed this.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nordine |first=Michael |date=January 20, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet's Contract Doesn't Actually Prevent Him From Speaking Out Against Woody Allen — Report |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/01/timothee-chalamet-woody-allen-a-rainy-day-in-new-york-contract-1201919512/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220520183126/https://www.indiewire.com/2018/01/timothee-chalamet-woody-allen-a-rainy-day-in-new-york-contract-1201919512/ |archive-date=May 20, 2022 |access-date=May 20, 2022 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref> Chalamet donated his salary to the charities [[Time's Up (organization)|Time's Up]], [[Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual & Transgender Community Center|LGBT Center of New York]], and [[Rape, Abuse & Incest National Network|RAINN]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Harmon |first=Steph |date=August 8, 2017 |title=Timothée Chalamet: 'I don't want to profit from my work on Woody Allen's film' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/jan/16/timothee-chalamet-i-dont-want-to-profit-from-my-work-on-woody-allens-film |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919122114/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/jan/16/timothee-chalamet-i-dont-want-to-profit-from-my-work-on-woody-allens-film |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=May 20, 2022 |website=[[The Guardian]] |location=London}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ng |first=David |date=September 16, 2018 |title=A year into #MeToo, some movies, including four Weinstein titles, are still stuck in distribution limbo |url=http://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-metoo-orphaned-movies-20180916-story.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919202246/http://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-metoo-orphaned-movies-20180916-story.html |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=September 20, 2018 |location=Los Angeles, California |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Pulver |first=Andrew |date=November 20, 2018 |title='A terrible shame': Jude Law defends Woody Allen film after Amazon shelves it |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/nov/20/jude-law-shelving-woody-allen-amazon-studios-shame-rainy-day-new-york |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204045054/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/nov/20/jude-law-shelving-woody-allen-amazon-studios-shame-rainy-day-new-york |archive-date=December 4, 2018 |access-date=December 4, 2018 |location=London, England |magazine=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> and did not promote the film.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pulver |first=Andrew |date=May 13, 2020 |title=Woody Allen's A Rainy Day in New York tops global box office |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/may/13/woody-allen-rainy-day-in-new-york-tops-global-box-office |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200513202807/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/may/13/woody-allen-rainy-day-in-new-york-tops-global-box-office |archive-date=May 13, 2020 |access-date=October 30, 2021 |website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> Allen claimed in his 2020 memoir ''[[Apropos of Nothing]]'' that Chalamet told Allen's sister [[Letty Aronson]] that he only denounced him in an attempt to improve his chances of winning an Academy Award for ''Call Me by Your Name''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Nolfi |first=Joey |date=March 25, 2020 |title=Woody Allen claims Timothée Chalamet denounced him to win an Oscar |url=https://ew.com/movies/woody-allen-timothee-chalamet-rainy-day-new-york/ |url-status=live |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220520183126/https://ew.com/movies/woody-allen-timothee-chalamet-rainy-day-new-york/ |archive-date=May 20, 2022 |access-date=May 20, 2022}}</ref>

Chalamet next portrayed [[Henry V of England]], a prince who, as a young man, becomes [[Kingdom of England|King of England]], in [[David Michôd]]'s [[Netflix]] period drama ''[[The King (2019 film)|The King]]'', based on several plays from [[Shakespeare]]'s [[Henriad]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wiseman |first=Andreas |date=May 31, 2018 |title=Robert Pattinson, Lily-Rose Depp, Among Cast Joining Timothée Chalamet In Netflix Pic 'The King', Cameras Roll This Week |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/robert-pattinson-lily-rose-depp-timothee-chalamet-netflix-movie-the-king-1202400703/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919122414/https://deadline.com/2018/05/robert-pattinson-lily-rose-depp-timothee-chalamet-netflix-movie-the-king-1202400703/ |archive-date=September 19, 2018 |access-date=June 3, 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref name="IndieWire-TheKing">{{Cite web |last=Sharf |first=Zack |date=July 25, 2019 |title='The King' First Look: All Hail Timothée Chalamet in Netflix's Shakespearean Drama |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/the-king-first-look-timothee-chalamet-netflix-1202160897/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725140818/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/the-king-first-look-timothee-chalamet-netflix-1202160897/ |archive-date=July 25, 2019 |access-date=July 25, 2019 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref> [[Richard Lawson (writer)|Richard Lawson]] of ''Vanity Fair'' wrote, "Chalamet does robust work, straightening his lanky posture as he goes, rising up into the role like a man ascendant".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lawson, Richard |date=September 2, 2019 |title=The King Review: Timothée Chalamet Gets an Actorly Coronation |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/09/timothee-chalamet-the-king-movie-review-netflix |url-status=live |url-access=limited |access-date=September 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191014155317/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/09/timothee-chalamet-the-king-movie-review-netflix |archive-date=October 14, 2019}}</ref> In his third film release of 2019, Chalamet portrayed [[Theodore "Laurie" Laurence]], a lovestruck teenager, in ''[[Little Women (2019 film)|Little Women]]'', an adaptation of [[Louisa May Alcott]]'s [[Little Women|novel of the same name]]. Marking his second collaboration with Gerwig and Ronan,<ref name="VF-LittleWomen">{{Cite news |last=Rich |first=Katey |date=September 8, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet Lost 20 Pounds for His Latest Role, but That Wasn't the Hard Part |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/09/timothee-chalamet-beautiful-boy-weight-loss |url-status=live |url-access=limited |access-date=September 30, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190803180048/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/09/timothee-chalamet-beautiful-boy-weight-loss |archive-date=August 3, 2019}}</ref> the film was acclaimed by critics,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Carras |first=Christi |date=February 9, 2020 |title=The only Oscar 'Little Women' won was for costume design |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/movies/story/2020-02-09/oscars-2020-little-women-greta-gerwig-costume-design |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200210090147/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/movies/story/2020-02-09/oscars-2020-little-women-greta-gerwig-costume-design |archive-date=February 10, 2020 |access-date=June 15, 2020 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref> two of whom{{mdash}}[[Peter Travers]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' and [[Ann Hornaday]] of ''[[The Washington Post]]''{{mdash}}also praised Chalamet's performance; Travers noted that the actor portrays the role with "innate charm and poignant vulnerability", while Hornaday highlighted his "languidly graceful" performance and its "playful physicality".<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Travers |first=Peter |author-link=Peter Travers |date=December 23, 2019 |title=Greta Gerwig Delivers a 'Little Women' for a New Generation |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/little-women-movie-review-greta-gerwig-927488/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408031405/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/little-women-movie-review-greta-gerwig-927488/ |archive-date=April 8, 2020 |access-date=September 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Hornaday |first=Ann |author-link=Ann Hornaday |date=December 17, 2019 |title=Part Alcott, part Gerwig, 'Little Women' is a very nearly perfect film |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/part-alcott-part-gerwig-little-women-is-a-very-nearly-perfect-film/2019/12/17/ce2ae21e-1eb0-11ea-87f7-f2e91143c60d_story.html?arc404=true |url-status=live |url-access=limited |access-date=September 11, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218141946/https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/part-alcott-part-gerwig-little-women-is-a-very-nearly-perfect-film/2019/12/17/ce2ae21e-1eb0-11ea-87f7-f2e91143c60d_story.html?arc404=true |archive-date=December 18, 2019}}</ref> Chalamet hosted an episode of the sketch comedy series ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' in 2020.<ref name="EW-SNL">{{Cite magazine |last=Hoglund |first=Andy |date=December 12, 2020 |title=Saturday Night Live recap: Timothée Chalamet makes his hosting debut |url=https://ew.com/tv/recaps/saturday-night-live-season-46-episode-8/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201213090356/https://ew.com/tv/recaps/saturday-night-live-season-46-episode-8/ |archive-date=December 13, 2020 |access-date=December 13, 2020}}</ref>

===2021–present: Established actor===
In 2021, Chalamet portrayed a student revolutionary in [[Wes Anderson]]'s ensemble comedy-drama ''[[The French Dispatch]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=December 6, 2018 |title=Timothee Chalamet Joins Tilda Swinton, Bill Murray in Wes Anderson's "The French Dispatch" |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/timothee-chalamet-wes-andersons-the-french-dispatch-1202970578/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181206235405/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/timothee-chalamet-wes-andersons-the-french-dispatch-1202970578/ |archive-date=December 6, 2018 |access-date=December 6, 2018 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Stolworthy |first=Jacob |date=February 1, 2019 |title=The French Dispatch: Every actor who will star in Wes Anderson's new film |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/the-french-dispatch-cast-list-wes-anderson-new-film-timothee-chalamet-kate-winslet-alex-lawther-a8758271.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308085313/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/the-french-dispatch-cast-list-wes-anderson-new-film-timothee-chalamet-kate-winslet-alex-lawther-a8758271.html |archive-date=March 8, 2019 |access-date=March 7, 2019 |website=[[The Independent]]}}</ref> The film had its world premiere at the [[2021 Cannes Film Festival]], where it generated positive reviews.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sharf |first=Zack |date=May 27, 2021 |title=Wes Anderson's 'French Dispatch' to Open in Theaters This October, Plus Cannes and NYFF |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2021/05/french-dispatch-release-date-october-cannes-nyff-1234640592/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210527134912/https://www.indiewire.com/2021/05/french-dispatch-release-date-october-cannes-nyff-1234640592/ |archive-date=May 27, 2021 |access-date=May 27, 2021 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref> Anderson wrote the role with Chalamet in mind.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sharf |first=Zack |date=October 16, 2020 |title=Why Wes Anderson Cast Timothée Chalamet: He Belongs in the French New Wave |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/10/wes-anderson-casting-timothee-chalamet-french-dispatch-1234592984/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210918180431/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/10/wes-anderson-casting-timothee-chalamet-french-dispatch-1234592984/ |archive-date=September 18, 2021 |access-date=October 24, 2021 |website=[[IndieWire]]}}</ref> Brianna Zigler of ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'' found him to be "perfectly attuned to Anderson's highly specified wavelength".<ref name="Paste-FrenchDispatch">{{Cite web |last=Zigler |first=Brianna |date=October 2, 2021 |title=The French Dispatch Proves Wes Anderson Isn't Going Anywhere |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/movies/the-french-dispatch-review/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211024094242/https://www.pastemagazine.com/movies/the-french-dispatch-review/ |archive-date=October 24, 2021 |access-date=October 24, 2021 |website=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]}}</ref> Chalamet starred as the main character [[Paul Atreides]] in [[Denis Villeneuve]]'s [[Dune (2021 film)|film adaptation]] of the science fiction novel ''[[Dune (novel)|Dune]]'', which premiered at the [[78th Venice International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Vivarelli |first=Nick |date=May 14, 2021 |title=Venice Fest Prepares to Roll Out Red Carpet for Full-Fledged Physical Edition (Exclusive) |url=https://variety.com/2021/film/news/venice-film-festival-2021-dune-films-red-carpet-1234972195/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514181308/https://variety.com/2021/film/news/venice-film-festival-2021-dune-films-red-carpet-1234972195/ |archive-date=May 14, 2021 |access-date=May 14, 2021 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> Villeneuve stated that Chalamet was his only choice to play the role: "I needed that for the audience to believe this young man will be able to lead a whole planet."<ref name="USAToday-Dune">{{Cite web |last=Ryan |first=Patrick |date=October 20, 2021 |title=Timothée Chalamet learned this new skill from 'Dune': 'I hope I won't have to use it' |url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/movies/2021/10/20/timothee-chalamet-dune-denis-villeneuve-rebecca-ferguson/8424993002/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021124507/https://eu.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/movies/2021/10/20/timothee-chalamet-dune-denis-villeneuve-rebecca-ferguson/8424993002/ |archive-date=October 21, 2021 |access-date=October 24, 2021 |website=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> Chalamet received positive reviews for his performance, with ''The Hollywood Reporter''{{'}}s David Rooney praising his "magnetic pensiveness [that] gives the coming-of-age element some heart" and Lewis Knight of ''[[Daily Mirror]]'' writing that "Timothée Chalamet completes his ascension to Hollywood leading man status".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rooney |first=David |date=September 3, 2021 |title=Timothee Chalamet in Denis Villeneuve's Dune Film Review Venice 2021 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/timothee-chalamet-in-denis-villeneuves-dune-film-review-venice-2021-1235005184/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026093836/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/timothee-chalamet-in-denis-villeneuves-dune-film-review-venice-2021-1235005184/ |archive-date=October 26, 2021 |access-date=October 24, 2021 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Knight |first=Lewis |date=October 19, 2021 |title=Dune review: Timothee Chalamet leads the sci-fi epic of a generation |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/film/dune-review-timothee-chalamet-leads-25245149 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026201456/https://www.mirror.co.uk/film/dune-review-timothee-chalamet-leads-25245149 |archive-date=October 26, 2021 |access-date=October 24, 2021 |website=[[Daily Mirror]]}}</ref> ''Dune'' earned over $400 million worldwide to emerge as his highest-grossing release.<ref>{{Cite Box Office Mojo |id=1160419 |title=Dune |access-date=March 25, 2022}}</ref> In his final role of the year, Chalamet played a skater punk in [[Adam McKay]]'s Netflix ensemble comedy film ''[[Don't Look Up]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=October 14, 2020 |title=Leonardo DiCaprio, Meryl Streep, Jonah Hill, Timothée Chalamet, Ariana Grande, Cate Blanchett, Others Join Jennifer Lawrence In Netflix's 'Don't Look Up' For Adam McKay |url=https://deadline.com/2020/10/netflix-adam-mckay-jennifer-lawrence-dont-look-up-leonardo-dicaprio-meryl-streep-jonah-hill-timothee-chalamet-ariana-grande-among-others-to-join-ensemble-1234596652/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201014200533/https://deadline.com/2020/10/netflix-adam-mckay-jennifer-lawrence-dont-look-up-leonardo-dicaprio-meryl-streep-jonah-hill-timothee-chalamet-ariana-grande-among-others-to-join-ensemble-1234596652/ |archive-date=October 14, 2020 |access-date=October 14, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref> It received mixed reviews from critics.<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 8, 2021 |title=Don't Look Up: Mixed reviews for Leonardo DiCaprio satire |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-59575497 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211131619/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-59575497 |archive-date=December 11, 2021 |access-date=May 28, 2022 |publisher=[[BBC News]]}}</ref> [[Justin Chang]] of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' found Chalamet "sweetly sincere" in his small part.<ref name="LATimes-DontLookUp">{{Cite web |last=Chang |first=Justin |date=December 7, 2021 |title='Don't Look Up' review: Scattershot Netflix satire |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/movies/story/2021-12-07/dont-look-up-review-netflix-dicaprio-lawrence |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211210220830/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/movies/story/2021-12-07/dont-look-up-review-netflix-dicaprio-lawrence |archive-date=December 10, 2021 |access-date=December 12, 2021 |website=[[Los Angeles Times]] |authorlink=Justin Chang}}</ref> The ensemble cast of the film was nominated for a [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture|SAG Award]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |date=January 12, 2022 |title=SAG Awards Nominations: 'House Of Gucci', 'Power Of The Dog', 'Succession', 'Ted Lasso' Top Lists |url=https://www.deadline.com/2022/01/sag-awards-nominations-2020-list-film-tv-nomineees-screen-actors-guild-1234908756 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220129234412/https://deadline.com/2022/01/sag-awards-nominations-2020-list-film-tv-nominees-screen-actors-guild-1234908756/ |archive-date=January 29, 2022 |access-date=January 12, 2022 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref>

Chalamet reunited with Guadagnino in the road film ''[[Bones and All]]'' (2022), in which he starred alongside [[Taylor Russell]] as cannibal drifters.<ref name="Deadline-BonesAll">{{Cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=January 28, 2021 |title=Hot Package: Luca Guadagnino Eyes New Project 'Bones & All' With Timothée Chalamet And Taylor Russell Circling Lead Roles |url=https://deadline.com/2021/01/timothee-chalamet-taylor-russell-luca-guadagninos-bones-all-1234682626/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128200045/https://deadline.com/2021/01/timothee-chalamet-taylor-russell-luca-guadagninos-bones-all-1234682626/ |archive-date=January 28, 2021 |access-date=January 28, 2021 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref> The project marked his first production venture, and he credited Guadagnino for mentoring him through the process.<ref>{{cite news|last=Dalton|first=Ben|date=September 2, 2022|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/timothee-chalamet-talks-bones-and-all-in-venice-societal-collapse-is-in-the-air/5174054.article|title=Timothée Chalamet talks 'Bones And All' in Venice: "Societal collapse is in the air"|work=Screen Daily|access-date=November 24, 2022|archive-date=September 2, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220902140607/https://www.screendaily.com/news/timothee-chalamet-talks-bones-and-all-in-venice-societal-collapse-is-in-the-air/5174054.article|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Bones and All'' premiered at the [[79th Venice International Film Festival]]. Leila Latif of ''[[IndieWire]]'' praised the chemistry between Chalamet and Russell and took note of his "near-peerless ability to gently weep",<ref name="Latif">{{cite news|last=Latif|first=Leila|date=September 2, 2022|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2022/09/bones-and-all-review-timothee-chalamet-cannibal-taylor-russell-1234757882/|title='Bones & All' Review: Chalamet Seduces, but a New Star Is Born in Cannibal Romance|work=IndieWire|access-date=September 29, 2022|archive-date=September 29, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220929220140/https://www.indiewire.com/2022/09/bones-and-all-review-timothee-chalamet-cannibal-taylor-russell-1234757882/|url-status=live}}</ref> and Jon Frosch of ''The Hollywood Reporter'' added that "Chalamet reminded us why he's the best actor of his generation".<ref name="Latif"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/best-film-performances-year-cate-blanchett-lea-seydoux-timothee-chalamet-danielle-deadwyler-1235275333/|title=Critics' Conversation: The Great Film Performances of 2022|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=6 December 2022|accessdate=7 December 2022|archive-date=December 7, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221207215127/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/best-film-performances-year-cate-blanchett-lea-seydoux-timothee-chalamet-danielle-deadwyler-1235275333/|url-status=live}}</ref> That same year, he lent his voice to the Netflix [[adult animated]] musical special ''[[Entergalactic (TV special)|Entergalactic]]''.<ref name="Petski">{{Cite web |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=2022-06-08 |title='Entergalactic': Jessica Williams, Timothée Chalamet, Vanessa Hudgens, Macaulay Culkin & More Join Kid Cudi In Voice Cast Of Netflix Animated Series |url=https://deadline.com/2022/06/entergalactic-jessica-williams-timothee-chalamet-vanessa-hudgens-macaulay-culkin-kid-cudi-voice-cast-netflix-animated-series-1235040732/ |access-date=2022-06-08 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=June 17, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220617142557/https://deadline.com/2022/06/entergalactic-jessica-williams-timothee-chalamet-vanessa-hudgens-macaulay-culkin-kid-cudi-voice-cast-netflix-animated-series-1235040732/ |url-status=live }}</ref> 

In 2023, Chalamet hosted another episode of ''Saturday Night Live''.<ref name="Variety-SNL">{{Cite magazine |last=Brew|first=Caroline|date=October 28, 2023|title='SNL' Announces Timothee Chalamet as Host With Boygenius as Musical Guest|url=https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/snl-timothee-chalamet-host-boygenius-musical-guest-1235771062/
|magazine=Variety |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20231029040626/https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/snl-timothee-chalamet-host-boygenius-musical-guest-1235771062/|archive-date=October 29, 2023 |access-date=November 11, 2023}}</ref> He then portrayed [[Willy Wonka]] in the musical film ''[[Wonka (film)|Wonka]]'', directed by [[Paul King (director)|Paul King]], for which he was paid $9 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Lang |first1=Brent |last2=Donnelly |first2=Matt |last3=Rubin |first3=Rebecca |date=20 July 2022 |title=Inside Movie Stars' Salaries: Joaquin Phoenix Nabs $20M for ''Joker 2'', Tom Cruise Heads to Over $100M and More |url=https://variety.com/2022/film/features/movie-star-salaries-joaquin-phoenix-joker-2-tom-cruise-1235320046/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220720160107/https://variety.com/2022/film/features/movie-star-salaries-joaquin-phoenix-joker-2-tom-cruise-1235320046/ |archive-date=20 July 2022 |access-date=7 October 2023 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> Chalamet was King's only choice for the role, stating that he cast the actor without an audition after seeing his high school performances on YouTube that proved his singing and dancing skills.<ref>{{cite magazine |title='Wonka' Director Can't Wait for You to See Hugh Grant's Sassy Oompa Loompa|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv-movies/tv-movie-features/wonka-trailer-paul-king-timothee-chalamet-hugh-grant-oompa-loompa-youtube-1234785386/|last=Zemler|first=Emily |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=28 November 2023 |date=July 11, 2023}}</ref> Chalamet sang seven songs for the [[Wonka (soundtrack)|film's soundtrack]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Saunders |first1=Toby |title=Wonka soundtrack: What songs are in new Timothée Chalamet film? |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/movies/wonka-soundtrack/ |website=Radio Times |access-date=December 5, 2023 |date=November 30, 2023 }}</ref> ''[[Slant Magazine]]''{{'s}} Derek Smith commended Chalamet for "imbuing Wonka [with] a warmth and tenderness that’s in perfect unison with the vibrant and bizarre world that King creates here".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Smith |first1=Derek |title=Wonka Review: A Delightfully Inventive Confection with Dollops of Menace |url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/film/wonka-review-timothee-chalamet-paul-king/ |website=Slant |access-date=December 5, 2023 |date=December 4, 2023 }}</ref> His performance earned him a nomination for another [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor – Motion Picture Musical or Comedy|Golden Globe Award for Best Actor]].<ref name="ggnom23">{{cite web |last1=Hipes |first1=Patrick |title=Golden Globe Nominations: 'Barbie', 'Oppenheimer' Top Movie List; 'Succession' Leads Way In TV |url=https://deadline.com/2023/12/golden-globe-nominations-2024-1235660995/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=December 11, 2023 |date=December 11, 2023}}</ref>

Chalamet will next reprise the role of Paul Atreides in the sequel to ''Dune'', titled ''[[Dune: Part Two]]''.<ref name="HollywoodReporter-DuneTwo">{{Cite web |last1=Couch |first1=Aaron |last2=McClintock |first2=Pamela |date=October 26, 2021 |title='Dune 2' a Go From Legendary, Warner Bros. |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/dune-2-greenlit-movie-release-date-1235036655/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026181508/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/dune-2-greenlit-movie-release-date-1235036655/ |archive-date=October 26, 2021 |access-date=October 29, 2021 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref><ref name="Wonka">{{Cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |date=March 9, 2022 |title=Warner Bros Release Dates: ''The Flash'' & ''Aquaman'' Moved To 2023; ''Wonka'', ''Shazam'' Sequel & Others Shift |url=https://deadline.com/2022/03/warner-bros-release-dates-the-flash-aquaman-wonka-shazam-sequel-1234974660/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220309204207/https://deadline.com/2022/03/warner-bros-release-dates-the-flash-aquaman-wonka-shazam-sequel-1234974660/ |archive-date=March 9, 2022 |access-date=March 9, 2022 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> He has also committed to portray [[Bob Dylan]] in the biopic ''A Complete Unknown'', directed by [[James Mangold]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2022/film/news/timothee-chalamet-prepped-bob-dylan-two-years-film-not-dead-1235433575/|title=Timothée Chalamet Has Prepped to Play Bob Dylan for Two Years, Says Biopic Isn't Dead: It's Going in a 'Very Positive Direction'|work=Variety|last=Sharf|first=Zach|date=November 16, 2022|access-date=December 28, 2022|archive-date=December 31, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231205222/https://variety.com/2022/film/news/timothee-chalamet-prepped-bob-dylan-two-years-film-not-dead-1235433575/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Public image and fashion==
[[File:Timothée Chalamet TIFF 2018.jpg|thumb|upright|Chalamet in 2018]]

Several media publications consider Chalamet to be among the most talented actors of his generation.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rose |first=Steve |date=June 1, 2020 |title=Move over, R-Patz: how Timothée Chalamet became the movie star of his generation |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/jun/01/timothee-chalamet-rainy-day-new-york |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502124431/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/jun/01/timothee-chalamet-rainy-day-new-york |archive-date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Coyle |first=Jake |date=September 9, 2018 |title=A year later, Timothee Chalamet is again turning heads |url=https://apnews.com/article/54287113343b41dc8d22ef8613f3f854 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502124432/https://apnews.com/article/54287113343b41dc8d22ef8613f3f854 |archive-date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref> Remarking upon his performance in ''Beautiful Boy,'' [[Kenneth Turan]] of the ''Los Angeles Times'' wrote that "he might be the male actor of his generation."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Turan |first=Kenneth |author-link=Kenneth Turan |date=October 11, 2018 |title=Review: Timothée Chalamet might be the male actor of his generation, and 'Beautiful Boy' is one reason why |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-beautiful-boy-review-timothee-chalamet-20181011-story.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506131252/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-beautiful-boy-review-timothee-chalamet-20181011-story.html |archive-date=May 6, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref> In 2018, he appeared in ''[[Forbes]]''{{'}}s [[Forbes 30 Under 30|30 Under 30]] Hollywood & Entertainment list.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Robehmed |first=Natalie |date=November 13, 2018 |title=From Timothée Chalamet To Zazie Beetz, The Hollywood 30 Under 30 Class Of 2019 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2018/11/13/from-timothee-chalamet-to-zazie-beetz-the-hollywood-30-under-30-class-of-2019/?sh=59ea4e1f2725 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502124432/https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2018/11/13/from-timothee-chalamet-to-zazie-beetz-the-hollywood-30-under-30-class-of-2019/?sh=59ea4e1f2725 |archive-date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[Forbes]]}}</ref>

Chalamet has been described by the media as a sex symbol<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ovenden |first=Olivia |date=January 14, 2019 |title='Beautiful Boy' Shows 2019 Will Be The Year Of Timothée Chalamet (Again) |url=https://www.esquire.com/uk/culture/film/a25561469/beautiful-boy-shows-2019-will-be-the-year-of-timothee-chalamet-again/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211103025156/https://www.esquire.com/uk/culture/film/a25561469/beautiful-boy-shows-2019-will-be-the-year-of-timothee-chalamet-again/ |archive-date=November 3, 2021 |access-date=November 2, 2021 |website=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] |language=en |quote=Though its title could easily be a nod to Chalamet's status as the millennial sex symbol ''du jour,'' ''Beautiful Boy'' really refers to his character, Nic Sheff...}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Holt |first=Brianna |date=December 19, 2019 |title=Film showed women that softboys are the emotionally intelligent men they wanted all along |url=https://qz.com/1772566/film-changed-the-softboy-trend-now-it-fights-toxic-masculinity/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211103025146/https://qz.com/1772566/film-changed-the-softboy-trend-now-it-fights-toxic-masculinity/ |archive-date=November 3, 2021 |access-date=November 2, 2021 |website=[[Quartz (publication)|Quartz]] |language=en |quote=Chalamet's resume of soft and atypical performances has redefined the Hollywood male sex symbol as a cisgender guy coded in stereotypically female characteristics.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Jacobs |first=Matthew |date=July 24, 2018 |title=What It Was Like To Meet Timothée Chalamet Before He Was A 'Sex Symbol' |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/timothee-chalamet-hot-summer-nights_n_5b561da6e4b0fd5c73c7dcf9 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211103025146/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/timothee-chalamet-hot-summer-nights_n_5b561da6e4b0fd5c73c7dcf9 |archive-date=November 3, 2021 |access-date=November 2, 2021 |website=[[HuffPost]] |language=en |quote='I thought he was gonna be a big actor one day,' Bynum said. 'What I don’t think anyone expected was he was going to become this kind of international sex symbol that came out of nowhere.'}}</ref> and a fashion icon,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Marain |first=Par Alexandre |date=April 3, 2020 |title=13 times Timothée Chalamet ruled the red carpet |url=https://www.vogue.fr/vogue-hommes-en/galerie/7-times-timothee-chalamet-owned-the-red-carpet-with-his-fashion-forward-style |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210504144854/https://www.vogue.fr/vogue-hommes-en/galerie/7-times-timothee-chalamet-owned-the-red-carpet-with-his-fashion-forward-style |archive-date=May 4, 2021 |access-date=May 4, 2021 |website=[[Vogue Paris]]}}</ref> with his hair, jawline, and [[Androgyny|androgynous]] looks highlighted as his trademarks.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Messina |first=Victoria |date=January 15, 2020 |title=An Ode to Timothée Chalamet's Chiseled, Sharp, and Sexy Jawline |url=https://www.popsugar.co.uk/celebrity/timothee-chalamet-jawline-pictures-47112605 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502174145/https://www.popsugar.co.uk/celebrity/timothee-chalamet-jawline-pictures-47112605 |archive-date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[PopSugar]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Flynn |first=Brian |date=November 2, 2018 |title=Why Timothée Chalamet is the perfect heartthrob for 2018 |url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/43ejmn/timothee-chalamet-beautiful-boy-heartthrob |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502125933/https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/43ejmn/timothee-chalamet-beautiful-boy-heartthrob |archive-date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[i-D]]}}</ref> ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' named him the most influential man in fashion in 2019 and credits him for continuing "to ply the boundary between traditional masculinity and femininity," writing "those fashion choices are all the more impressive considering that Chalamet styles himself."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Yotka |first=Steff |date=November 18, 2018 |title=Timothée Chalamet Is the Most Influential Man in Fashion |url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/timothee-chalamet-is-the-most-influential-man-in-fashion |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502124431/https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/timothee-chalamet-is-the-most-influential-man-in-fashion |archive-date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]}}</ref> In 2020, ''[[GQ]]'' ranked him as the best-dressed man in the world,<ref>{{Cite web |last1=van den Broeke |first1=Teo |last2=Tong |first2=Alfred |date=December 4, 2019 |title=The 50 best-dressed men of 2020 |url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/fashion/gallery/best-dressed-men-2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210425054232/https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/fashion/gallery/best-dressed-men-2020 |archive-date=April 25, 2021 |access-date=May 2, 2021 |website=[[GQ]]}}</ref> and in 2023, Chalamet was voted Most Stylish Man of The Year by ''GQ'''s readers.<ref>{{cite web |date=December 22, 2023 |title=Timothée Chalamet Is GQ’s Most Stylish Man of the Year, as Voted by You |url=https://www.gq.com/story/most-stylish-man-2023/ |access-date=December 28, 2023 |website=GQ}}</ref>

Chalamet served as one of the co-chairs of the 2021 [[Met Gala]], alongside singer [[Billie Eilish]], professional tennis player [[Naomi Osaka]] and poet [[Amanda Gorman]]. The event was part of the [[Costume Institute]]'s exhibit ''In America: A Lexicon of Fashion.''<ref>{{Cite web |last=Okwodu |first=Janelle |date=May 3, 2021 |title=Timothée Chalamet, Billie Eilish, Naomi Osaka, and Amanda Gorman Will Co-chair the 2021 Met Gala |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/met-gala-2021-co-chairs-timothee-chalamet-billie-eilish-naomi-osaka-amanda-gorman |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503130822/https://www.vogue.com/article/met-gala-2021-co-chairs-timothee-chalamet-billie-eilish-naomi-osaka-amanda-gorman |archive-date=May 3, 2021 |access-date=May 8, 2021 |website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]}}</ref> That same year, Chalamet became a brand ambassador for [[Cartier (jeweler)|Cartier]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Godfrey |first=Deeney |date=September 3, 2021 |title=Cartier unveils Timothée Chalamet as the Maison's newest Friend of the House |url=https://ww.fashionnetwork.com/news/Cartier-unveils-timothee-chalamet-as-the-maison-s-newest-friend-of-the-house,1330810.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210903223117/https://ww.fashionnetwork.com/news/Cartier-unveils-timothee-chalamet-as-the-maison-s-newest-friend-of-the-house,1330810.html |archive-date=September 3, 2021 |access-date=September 4, 2021 |website=Fashion Network}}</ref> He also collaborated with [[Haider Ackermann]] to design a [[hoodie]] with 100% of the proceeds going to French organization Afghanistan Libre, which is centered around preserving the rights of women in Afghanistan.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hess |first=Liam |date=December 23, 2021 |title=Timothée Chalamet and Haider Ackermann Design a Hoodie for Afghan Women's Rights |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/timothee-chalamet-haider-ackermann-charity-hoodie |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211228203209/https://www.vogue.com/article/timothee-chalamet-haider-ackermann-charity-hoodie |archive-date=December 28, 2021 |access-date=December 28, 2021 |website=Vogue}}</ref>

At the [[94th Academy Awards]], Chalamet wore a sequined [[Louis Vuitton]] jacket from [[Nicolas Ghesquière]]'s womenswear collection without a shirt; ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'' declared that he had "rewritten the gentleman's Oscar dress code for good," highlighting the boundary-pushing outfit that "blurred the lines of fashion's traditional gender divide."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Munzenrieder |first=Kyle |date=September 3, 2021 |title=Timothée Chalamet Just Rewrote the Oscars Dress Code |url=https://www.wmagazine.com/fashion/timothee-chalamet-shirtless-2022-oscars-red-carpet |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328204634/https://www.wmagazine.com/fashion/timothee-chalamet-shirtless-2022-oscars-red-carpet |archive-date=March 28, 2022 |access-date=March 29, 2022 |website=[[W (magazine)|W]]}}</ref> He subsequently appeared on the cover of the October 2022 print edition of ''[[British Vogue]],'' becoming the first solo male to do so in the magazine's history.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Timothée Chalamet Is British Vogue's First Solo Male Cover Star|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/timothee-chalamet-british-vogue-october-2022|website=British Vogue|date=September 15, 2022|access-date=15 September 2022|archive-date=September 15, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220915140359/https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/timothee-chalamet-british-vogue-october-2022|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=The Chalamet Effect: Timothée Talks Fate, Fashion And Being An Old Soul|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/arts-and-lifestyle/article/timothee-chalamet-british-vogue-interview?utm_campaign=dashhudson&utm_medium=referral&utm_source=instagram&utm_content=www.instagram.com/p/CihuKj4M_QZ/|website=British Vogue|date=September 15, 2022|access-date=15 September 2022|archive-date=September 15, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220915141049/https://www.vogue.co.uk/arts-and-lifestyle/article/timothee-chalamet-british-vogue-interview?utm_campaign=dashhudson&utm_medium=referral&utm_source=instagram&utm_content=www.instagram.com/p/CihuKj4M_QZ/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In 2023, Chalamet became the face of [[Chanel]]'s men's fragrance [[Bleu de Chanel]], taking over from the late French actor [[Gaspard Ulliel]]. The advertising campaign starring Chalamet and shot by photographer [[Mario Sorrenti]] was released in June, with a campaign film directed by [[Martin Scorsese]] coming in the fall.<ref name="Chanel">{{Cite web|last=Nnadi|first=Chioma|title=Timothée Chalamet on French-Guy Hair, Filming With Scorsese, and Being the New Face of Bleu de Chanel|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/chanel-bleu-ambassador-interview|website= Vogue|date=May 15, 2023|access-date= May 15, 2023|archive-date=May 15, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230515135026/https://www.vogue.com/article/chanel-bleu-ambassador-interview|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Leo|first=Amanda|title=Timothée Chalamet Ushers In An Audacious Era Of Masculinity As The New Bleu De Chanel Ambassador |url=https://elle.com.sg/2023/05/15/timothee-chalamet-ushers-in-an-audacious-era-of-masculinity-as-the-new-bleu-de-chanel-ambassador/|website=Elle|date=May 15, 2023|access-date= May 15, 2023|archive-date=May 15, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230515144928/https://elle.com.sg/2023/05/15/timothee-chalamet-ushers-in-an-audacious-era-of-masculinity-as-the-new-bleu-de-chanel-ambassador/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Timothée Chalamet has been named the new ambassador for Bleu de Chanel |url=https://thefashionenthusiast.uk/stories/timothee-chalamet-has-been-named-the-new-ambassador-for-bleu-de-chanel|website=The Fashion Enthusiast|date=May 15, 2023|access-date= May 15, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230516103417/https://thefashionenthusiast.uk/stories/timothee-chalamet-has-been-named-the-new-ambassador-for-bleu-de-chanel|archive-date=May 16, 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> He reportedly received $35 million dollars for his involvement in the campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|title=How UTA's Dan Constable Put the Hollywood Agency on the Luxury Fashion Map|url=https://wwd.com/business-news/business-features/uta-dan-constable-hollywood-luxury-fashion-dealmaking-1235820791/|website=[[Women's Wear Daily|WWD]]|date=September 25, 2023|access-date=October 16, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230926014440/https://wwd.com/business-news/business-features/uta-dan-constable-hollywood-luxury-fashion-dealmaking-1235820791/|archive-date=September 26, 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> That same year he teamed up with Cartier to make a costume necklace, influenced by his character of Willy Wonka. Chalamet met with creative director Marie-Laure Cérède to design the necklace, having previously researched the history of the brand, he took inspiration form their more colorful '60s and '70s period. It took 450 hours to create, and it is made of [[onyx]], [[emeralds]], [[tourmaline|pink tourmalines]], [[rubellite|rubellites]] and [[opal|blue opals]].<ref>{{Cite web|title="It's Insane, Right?" Timothée Worked With Cartier On His Custom Candy-Inspired Wonka Necklace|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/timothee-chalamet-wonka-necklace-cartier|website=[[British Vogue]]|date=November 28, 2023|first=Kerry|last=McDermott}}</ref> Chalamet collaborated with [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]] on a pair of [[Nike Dunk|Dunk Lows]], also inspired by the character. The sneakers were created by Chalamet and the Nike team at their [[Nike World Headquarters|headquarters]] in Beaverton, and their general appearance is based on the inner and outer lining of the jacket worn by his character in the movie. The sneakers are hand-embroidered, and only eight pairs were made.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Timothée Chalamet's 'Wonka' Nike Dunks Are Limited to Five Pairs: 'It's Sort of Unbelievable'|url=https://www.complex.com/sneakers/a/mike-destefano/timothee-chalamet-wonka-nike-dunk|website=[[Complex Networks|Complex]]|date=November 30, 2023|first=Mike|last=Destefano|access-date=December 1, 2023}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Chalamet splits his time between New York and California.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Riley |first=Daniel |date=October 15, 2020 |title=The Making (and Remaking) of Timothée Chalamet |url=https://www.gq.com/story/timothee-chalamet-november-2020-cover-profile |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115005438/https://www.gq.com/story/timothee-chalamet-november-2020-cover-profile |archive-date=January 15, 2022 |access-date=January 14, 2022 |website=[[GQ]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://manofmany.com/living/timothee-chalamet-kate-uptons-estate-18-million |title=Timothée Chalamet Buys Kate Upton's Plush Mountain Estate for $18 Million |first=Sam |last=Mangioni |date=October 21, 2022 |newspaper=[[Man of Many]] |access-date=October 21, 2022 |archive-date=October 20, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221020065324/https://manofmany.com/living/timothee-chalamet-kate-uptons-estate-18-million |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite significant media attention and public interest, he rarely discusses the romantic aspects of his personal life.<ref name=":0" />

Chalamet is an avid sports fan; in his youth, he aspired to be a professional [[football player]].<ref name="Verge" /> He is a lifelong supporter of the basketball team [[New York Knicks]] and the French football team [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Martin |first=Emmie |date=March 2, 2018 |title=22-year-old Oscar-nominee Timothée Chalamet's 1st big splurge was on Knicks tickets |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/03/02/oscar-nominee-timothee-chalamets-1st-big-splurge-knicks-tickets.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113215555/https://www.cnbc.com/2018/03/02/oscar-nominee-timothee-chalamets-1st-big-splurge-knicks-tickets.html |archive-date=January 13, 2022 |access-date=January 14, 2022 |website=[[CNBC]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Aubin |first=Maxime |date=November 1, 2019 |title=Timothée Chalamet fan de Saint-Etienne chez Seth Meyers |url=https://frenchmorning.com/timothee-chalamet-fan-de-saint-etienne-chez-seth-meyers/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118184157/https://frenchmorning.com/timothee-chalamet-fan-de-saint-etienne-chez-seth-meyers/ |archive-date=January 18, 2022 |access-date=January 16, 2022 |website=[[L'Équipe]]}}</ref> He enjoys [[hip-hop music]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=Graham |first=Adam |date=October 24, 2018 |title='Beautiful Boy' Timothée Chalamet aims to keep level head |url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/entertainment/movies/2018/10/25/movie-beautiful-boy-actor-timothee-chalamet-aims-keep-level-head/1740825002/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113220530/https://www.detroitnews.com/story/entertainment/movies/2018/10/25/movie-beautiful-boy-actor-timothee-chalamet-aims-keep-level-head/1740825002/ |archive-date=January 13, 2022 |access-date=January 13, 2022 |website=[[The Detroit News]]}}</ref> and considers rapper [[Kid Cudi]] to be his biggest career inspiration.<ref name="GQ" />

